lead_paragraph: The Walt Disney Company, bruised by the unprofitable Euro Disneyland, has not backed off from its plans to build a second theme park in Southern California, a company executive says. Mounting losses from Euro Disneyland and the recent departure of a key executive have prompted speculation that Disney may be reassessing its plans for the proposed $3 billion Westcot park. High development costs have also raised doubts about the project.

headline.main: Disney Says It Still Plans a 2d Southern California Park
